Adjust rack to top position and preheat oven to 425 degrees.

Drain and rinse @chickpeas{13.4%ounce}; pat dry with #paper towels{}. Toss on a #baking sheet{} with a large drizzle of @olive oil{2%teaspoon}, @Shawarma Spice Blend{1%tablespoon}, @salt{} and @pepper{}.

> Be sure to measure the Shawarma Spice—we sent more.

Roast on top rack until browned and crisp, ~{18-20%minutes}.

> It's natural for chickpeas to pop a bit while roasting.

While chickpeas roast, in a #small pot{}, combine @bulgur wheat{1/2%cup}, @water{1%cup}, @harissa powder{1/2%tablespoon}, and @salt{1/2%tsp}. Bring to a boil, then cover and reduce to a low simmer. Cook until water has absorbed and bulgur is tender, ~{12-15%minutes}.

> For 4 servings, use 2 cups water, all the harissa powder, and 1 tsp salt.

Keep covered off heat until ready to serve. Drain bulgur if necessary, then fluff with a #fork{}.

While bulgur cooks, wash and dry all produce.

Trim and halve @Persian cucumber{1}(trimmed and sliced) lengthwise; thinly slice crosswise into ¼-inch-thick half-moons. Dice @Roma tomato{1}(diced). Pick and finely chop fronds from @dill{1/4%ounce}(picked and finely chopped). Halve, peel, and thinly slice @shallot{1}(halved, peeled, and thinly sliced).

In a #medium bowl{}, combine cucumber, tomato, @Feta cheese{1/2%cup}, chopped dill, and as much shallot as you like. Toss with @Greek vinaigrette{1.5%ounce} and season with salt and pepper.

> Save the rest of the vinaigrette for serving.

Wrap @flour tortillas{2} in damp paper towels and microwave until warm and pliable, ~{30%seconds}. Place tortillas on a clean work surface and spread bottom third of each with @roasted red pepper hummus{4%tablespoon}. Top with a heaping ¼ cup bulgur, ¼ cup chickpeas, and ¼ cup salad. Fold up bottom side of each tortilla over filling, then fold over left and right sides toward the filling. Roll up tortillas, starting with filled sides, to create wraps.

> For less mess, place each tortilla on a large piece of foil before rolling and wrap up with the foil. Simply unwrap as you eat!

Halve wraps on a diagonal; divide between plates along with remaining bulgur, chickpeas, and salad. Serve with remaining Greek vinaigrette on the side for drizzling or dipping.